metadata.name: Cave of Zeus
metadata.description: When the sky god Zeus angered his brother, the sea god Poseidon, he took refuge in this cave to wait for the calmness of Poseidon, who lifted his triple pitchfork and turned the waves upside down and turned the sea upside down, and took refuge in this cave and took a rest here, so the name of the cave remained "Zeus Cave". The goddess of beauty in mythology. It is said that Aphrodite became beautiful by swimming in the Cave of Zeus. Therefore, the water of the Cave of Zeus is believed to have a beautifying effect on the skin of women.
